cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a neural network for unsupervised anomaly detection, which is a common topic in machine learning and falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The proposed method is applied to both image and document datasets, indicating a potential application in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The use of a subspace recovery layer suggests a focus on dimensionality reduction and feature extraction, which are also relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data science (cs.DS). Finally, the use of a neural network implies a potential application in neural networks (cs.NE).
